## Passive — Tiempo de Papel Picado

Every **1.2 seconds**, Pixolotl stores a **PapelPicadoFrame** in a circular buffer of
**8 slots**. Each frame records:
- Position (Vector2)
- Current HP (float)

A translucent marigold-orange **ghost afterimage** (`PapelPicadoGhost`) is spawned at
each stored position. Ghosts fade from 70% alpha to 30% alpha over 10 s, then hold at
30% indefinitely until the corresponding frame is consumed by RANIBOBER (E), at which
point the ghost does a rapid forced fade (0.3 s) and is destroyed.

When the buffer is full (8 frames), the oldest frame is overwritten and its ghost is
force-faded.

> **Design note:** the ghosts are both a visual record of Pixolotl's recent path and
> the ammunition for her E skill. More ghosts = more rewind options. Enemies can see
> where she's been and anticipate possible rewind destinations.

---

## Abilities

### Basic Attack — Branquias (Gills)

**Magazine:** 3 volleys | **Fire rate:** 0.25 s between volleys | **Reload windup:** 0.75 s

Pixolotl opens her external gills and fires **6 bubbles simultaneously** per volley at
**fixed world-space angles**. The angles do **not** flip with facing direction — they
always fire in these absolute directions (degrees CCW from right):

| Gill | Angle | Direction |
|------|-------|-----------|
| 1 | 2° | Near-right |
| 2 | 25° | Low-right |
| 3 | 65° | Upper-right |
| 4 | 115° | Upper-left |
| 5 | 155° | Low-left |
| 6 | 178° | Near-left |

**Bubble behavior:**
- Travel along straight-line Bézier curves (control points on the line; effectively
  straight infinite flight)
- Endpoint distance: **200 units** (functionally infinite — bubbles fly until they hit
  something or leave the arena)
- Bubbles crack on terrain contact (Ground / Platform layers)
- Bubbles deal **30 base damage** on contact with enemies (Player / Foe layers)
- All live bubbles register with Pixolotl and query `BulletSpeedMultiplier` each frame
  — SOBRECARGA instantly accelerates all existing bubbles

Bubble spawning is driven by the **Animation Event** `OnBranquiasFire()` — `HandleBA`
only gates on ammo and triggers the animator.

> **Design note:** the fixed world-space angles mean Pixolotl's firing pattern is
> position-dependent, not aim-dependent. She fires in a wide fan that covers both
> sides equally. This makes her positioning — not her aim — the skill expression.
> Moving left or right shifts which bubbles reach which parts of the arena.

---

### Shift — SOBRECARGA (Overcharge)

**Cooldown:** 12.8 s | **Duration:** 3.2 s

Pixolotl accelerates her personal time. During SOBRECARGA:

| Parameter | Normal | SOBRECARGA |
|-----------|--------|------------|
| Move speed | 4 m/s | **6.4 m/s** (1.6×) |
| Fire rate (volley interval) | 0.25 s | **0.15 s** (1.67× faster) |
| Reload windup | 0.75 s | **0.5 s** |
| Bullet speed | 1.0× | **1.6×** (all live bubbles instantly) |
| Gravity scale | 1.0 | **0.6** (floaty) |

- **VFX:** looping particle system plays; TrailRenderer enabled for motion smear
- All live bubbles query `BulletSpeedMultiplier` each frame — activating SOBRECARGA
  instantly accelerates every bubble currently in flight; deactivating snaps them
  back to normal speed

> **Design note:** SOBRECARGA is Pixolotl's burst window. The 3.2 s duration creates
> urgency — reposition, fire all 3 volleys at the faster rate, and use the bullet-speed
> boost to catch enemies off-guard. The 12.8 s cooldown (4× the duration) means it's
> available roughly once per combat engagement.

---

### E — RANIBOBER (Rewind)

**Max stacks:** 8 | **Charge time:** 2.5 s per stack | **Inner CD:** 0.25 s

Pixolotl rewinds her personal timeline. Consumes **1 stack + 1 stored PapelPicadoFrame**
(the newest frame). On activation:

1. **Teleport** — instantly move to the consumed frame's position
2. **Heal** — recover **50% of HP lost** since that frame was stored
3. **Invincibility** — 0.1 s on arrival
4. **AoE burst** at arrival position:
   - **5 m radius**
   - **40 damage** to all enemies
   - **0.3 s stun** to all enemy characters
5. **Rewind all live bubbles** — each bubble moves backward along its Bézier path by
   `elapsedPassiveTimer × bubble's current speed` units
6. **Ghost cleanup** — the consumed frame's ghost does a rapid 0.3 s forced fade

The passive frame timer resets after consumption (set to the gap since the
second-newest frame, or 0 if no frames remain).

**Requirements:** at least 1 stack AND at least 1 stored frame.

> **Design note:** RANIBOBER is both escape and engage. Rewinding to a frame from 1.2 s
> ago is a short hop; rewinding to a frame from ~9.6 s ago (full buffer) is a
> cross-arena teleport. The 50% heal rewards using it after taking damage — the more
> HP lost since the frame, the more value. The bubble rewind adds zoning complexity:
> bubbles that passed an enemy fly backward and can hit again.

